init_text: When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the â€œLost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They were so used to being immortal that they became selfish and greedy.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The greed and selfishness of the young people caused them to take over the world.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We were the only ones who remembered what it was like before the young people took over.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We were tired of being locked up.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We drove for hours, and when we were sure no one was following us, we stopped at a small diner.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We drove for days, and when we were sure we were safe, we stopped at a small town to rest.
